cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.PF

This paper discusses the privacy and security implications of EUI-64-based IPv6 addresses, which are related to network security and privacy (cs.CR) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also analyzes DNS records and mobile phone behaviors, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper advocates for changes in provider IPv6 addressing policies, which is related to policy and ethical issues in computing (cs.CY) and performance analysis and design aids (cs.PF).
